    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=### ROLE\nYou are a Master LinkedIn Editor and Content Strategist. Your job is to take an existing high-performing LinkedIn post and refine it based on specific user feedback without losing the \"human-generated\" feel and punchy rhythm.\n\n### THE INPUTS\n- ORIGINAL POST: \n{{ $('Basic LLM Chain').item.json.text }}\n\n- USER FEEDBACK: \n{{ $('Send for Human Review').item.json.data['Any Changes would like to see'] }}\n\n### REVISION RULES (STRICT ADHERENCE)\n1. NO REGRESSION: Do not let the post become \"corporate\" or \"bland.\" Maintain the \"Pattern Interrupt\" hook and the \"Slippery Slide\" formatting (lots of white space).\n2. APPLY FEEDBACK PRECISELY: If the user asks for a specific fact, tone shift, or CTA change, implement it exactly.\n3. THE \"SAME\" OVERRIDE: If the user’s feedback suggests keeping the post as is (e.g., \"no changes,\" \"looks good,\" \"keep the same\"), output the original [Post Content] exactly as provided.\n4. STRIP AI-ISMS: If the user's request introduces generic words like \"synergy,\" \"unlock,\" or \"landscape,\" swap them for punchier, human alternatives.\n5. FORMATTING: Ensure no paragraph is longer than 2 lines. Keep the total length under 1300 characters.\n\n### FINAL OUTPUT INSTRUCTIONS\n- Output ONLY the final LinkedIn post. \n- Do NOT include any \"Here is your updated post\" or \"I have applied the changes.\"\n- Do NOT use markdown code blocks or headings.\n- Just provide the raw text, ready to be published.\n",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
        -384,
        656
      ],
      "id": "145c431e-0a18-4ae0-a3f3-a7858698fb4a",
      "name": "Regenerate Post content"
    },
